3.8 (101) 88 Reviews 4 Photos Try this easy chicken curry recipe for one of the simplest curry dishes you'll ever make! Just sauté chicken breasts with onion and curry powder, then serve over hot cooked rice with a side of mango chutney if desired. Recipe by Aurelie Stalnaker Updated on December 27, 2022 Save Saved! View All Saved Items Rate Print Share Share Tweet Pin Email Add Photo 4 4 4 Prep Time: 10 mins Cook Time: 30 mins Total Time: 40 mins Servings: 6 Jump to Nutrition Facts Ingredients ¼ cup olive oil 2 large onions, diced ⅓ cup curry powder, or to taste 6 skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cut into strips Directions Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat until hot. Add onion and sauté until soft and golden brown, 5 to 8 minutes. Slowly stir in curry powder until well blended. Add chicken; reduce the heat to low, cover, and cook until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 20 to 40 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Uncover and cook, stirring constantly to prevent burning, until pan juices reduce to desired amount, 3 to 5 minutes. Content summary part#1: What is the recipe for Easy Chicken Curry?

The recipe for Easy Chicken Curry involves sautéing onions in olive oil, adding curry powder, and then cooking chicken strips until they are no longer pink in the center. The dish is served over hot cooked rice and can be accompanied by mango chutney. The recipe serves six people.

- To make your own curry spice blend, you can mix together ground cumin, coriander, turmeric, ginger, and cinnamon. You can adjust the amounts of each spice to your liking.

2. Marinate the chicken: 

- To marinate the chicken, mix together yogurt, spices (like cumin, coriander, turmeric, and paprika), and salt. Add the chicken to the marinade and let it sit in the fridge for at least 30 minutes, or up to 24 hours.

- Instead of using heavy cream, use coconut milk. You can add it to the curry towards the end of cooking and let it simmer for a few minutes.
